{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3302279,"name":"Jeff Lange","username":"jlange","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/82dd89/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T18:18:00.238Z","cooked":"<p>Hi there, We’re using the <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> phoenix 6 swerve drive libs based on the SwerveWithPathPlanner example github project from <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span>. Everything is driving as expected, however the estimated pose and telemetry is always showing the bot moving in the opposite direction when the driver station is set to the red alliance. (both x and y)</p>
<p>It’s basically as if the internal code that is tracking the x/y position of the bot is not inverting it’s logic when on Red.</p>
<p>Has anyone else run into this? or know a simple solution?<br>
Thanks!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T18:18:00.238Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":583,"reads":255,"readers_count":254,"score":2966.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Jeff Lange","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63996,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3302290,"name":"John Fogarty","username":"JohnFogarty","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/johnfogarty/{size}/267052_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T18:29:13.998Z","cooked":"<p>You need to setup your Field2D to use relative origin.</p>
