</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T18:29:13.998Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":18,"reads":238,"readers_count":237,"score":137.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"John Fogarty","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12688,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302382,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T19:51:17.146Z","cooked":"<p>When running a path?  Did you update the CommandServeDrive.java to look at the alliance?</p>
<p>(Updated version using the PathPlanner &amp; <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> examples below…)</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">private void configurePathPlanner() {
        double driveBaseRadius = 0;
        for (var moduleLocation : m_moduleLocations) {
            driveBaseRadius = Math.max(driveBaseRadius, moduleLocation.getNorm());
        }

        AutoBuilder.configureHolonomic(
                () -&gt; this.getState().Pose, // Supplier of current robot pose
                this::seedFieldRelative, // Consumer for seeding pose against auto
                this::getCurrentRobotChassisSpeeds,
                (speeds) -&gt; this.setControl(autoRequest.withSpeeds(speeds)), // Consumer of ChassisSpeeds to drive the
                                                                             // robot
                new HolonomicPathFollowerConfig(new PIDConstants(10, 0, 0),
                        new PIDConstants(10, 0, 0),
                        TunerConstants.kSpeedAt12VoltsMps,
                        driveBaseRadius,
                        new ReplanningConfig()),
                () -&gt; {
                    // Boolean supplier that controls when the path will be mirrored for the red
                    // alliance
                    // This will flip the path being followed to the red side of the field.
                    // THE ORIGIN WILL REMAIN ON THE BLUE SIDE

                    var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance();
                    if (alliance.isPresent()) {
                        return alliance.get() == DriverStation.Alliance.Red;
                    }
                    return false;
                }, // Change this if the path needs to be flipped on red vs blue
                this); // Subsystem for requirements
    }
</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T19:51:17.146Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":20,"reads":206,"readers_count":205,"score":146.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/3","custom_user_title":"Software Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302418,"name":"Jeff Lange","username":"jlange","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/82dd89/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T20:13:09.818Z","cooked":"<p>Yes, I made that change. The problem is not with following a path, that actually works perfect for both red and blue. The issue is with Teleop mode, The aprilTag system will detect the proper location on the field, and will call addVisionMeasurement() using the correct location. When looking at the shuffleboard field layout pose widget, the dot shows up in the exact location as expected, but as you start to drive away from the red wall, the the dot will move towards the wall, so it is internally adding to the X coordinate instead of subtracting.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T20:13:09.818Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":11,"reads":151,"readers_count":150,"score":85.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Jeff Lange","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":36169,"username":"Hollisms","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63996,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"+1","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302420,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T20:15:40.564Z","cooked":"<p><span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span>’s example code doesn’t make a choice about which field coordinate system you’re going to use. Notice <a href="https://github.com/CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples/blob/main/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/CommandSwerveDrivetrain.java#L65" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">that the alliance supplier always returns <code>false</code></a>. As <a class="mention" href="/u/hollisms">@Hollisms</a> points out, you need to decide that and add the proper code.</p>
<p>Take a look at the <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#field-coordinate-systems" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Field coordinate system</a> documentation. I highly recommend using <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#always-blue-origin" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Always blue origin</a> this year, as this is what PathPlanner does (NEW this year.) If you choose to do this, you’ll also need to update the <a href="https://github.com/CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples/blob/main/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java#L38" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">teleop driving code</a> to deal with the alliance, as noted in the <em>Always blue origin</em> documentation.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T20:15:40.564Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":148,"readers_count":147,"score":94.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples/blob/main/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java#L38","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Phoenix6-Examples/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java at main · CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples · GitHub","clicks":19},{"url":"https://github.com/CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples/blob/main/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/CommandSwerveDrivetrain.java#L65","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Phoenix6-Examples/java/SwerveWithPathPlanner/src/main/java/frc/robot/CommandSwerveDrivetrain.java at main · CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix6-Examples · GitHub","clicks":18},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#always-blue-origin","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Coordinate System — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":9},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#field-coordinate-systems","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Coordinate System — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":7}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/5","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302441,"name":"Jeff Lange","username":"jlange","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/82dd89/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T20:35:00.059Z","cooked":"<p><span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> support got back to me, and it turns out this is a known issue in their libs <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/frowning.png?v=12" title=":frowning:" class="emoji" alt=":frowning:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>
<blockquote>
<p>This is a known issue that we have resolved internally but don’t have a full release for yet.</p>
<p>The root of the problem is that most path following programs, including PathPlanner, assume the robot’s coordinates are always referenced to Blue Alliance’s right-most corner regardless of the current alliance, and the axis pointing to the Red Alliance wall indicates positive X.</p>
<p>Our code currently mimics that behavior, which works great for blue alliance operation and for pathplanner autonomous (regardless of alliance), but doesn’t work if you’re teleop-controlling in red alliance with field-centric (really operator-centric) controls.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>They did offer to make a dev release for me to test! so hopefully that will fix the issue.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T20:35:00.059Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":17,"reads":141,"readers_count":140,"score":133.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Jeff Lange","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":44380,"username":"gdefender","name":"Andy Gasser","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63996,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302466,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T21:02:12.580Z","cooked":"<p>While you wait for the release, it’s entirely possible to resolve it yourself. I think the upcoming release will be adding a feature to do more of the work for you. The library doesn’t have a bug that needs to be fixed.</p>
<p>To fix it, add a method to <code>RobotContainer</code> to determine if you need to invert the controls:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">private double invertForAlliance() {
  var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance();
  if (alliance.isPresent() &amp;&amp; alliance.get() == Alliance.Red) {
      return -1;
  }
  return 1;
}
</code></pre>
<p>EDIT: Fixed return value for blue alliance</p>
<p>Update the command for driving to call that method</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">drivetrain.setDefaultCommand( // Drivetrain will execute this command periodically
    drivetrain.applyRequest(() -&gt; drive.withVelocityX(-joystick.getLeftY() * MaxSpeed * invertForAlliance()) // Drive forward with
                                                                                                             // negative Y (forward)
        .withVelocityY(-joystick.getLeftX() * MaxSpeed * invertForAlliance()) // Drive left with negative X (left)
        .withRotationalRate(-joystick.getRightX() * MaxAngularRate) // Drive counterclockwise with negative X (left)
    ).ignoringDisable(true));
</code></pre>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T21:26:43.536Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":130,"readers_count":129,"score":81.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":63996,"username":"jlange","name":"Jeff Lange","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/82dd89/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/7","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302483,"name":"Jeff Lange","username":"jlange","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/82dd89/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T21:22:24.575Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks,<br>
I’ve actually already added equivalent code, so the bot is properly driving in the correct orientation. The issue is with the internal tracking of the current pose. The estimated pose is just going the wrong way, even though the bot is traveling in the correct direction.</p>
<p>And <a class="mention" href="/u/hollisms">@Hollisms</a> is correct, it should be 1 and -1</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2024-02-05T21:22:24.575Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":113,"readers_count":112,"score":42.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":453448,"topic_slug":"ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery","display_username":"Jeff Lange","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":44380,"username":"gdefender","name":"Andy Gasser","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63996,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/ctre-phoenix-6-swerve-pose-odemetery/453448/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3302488,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-05T21:29:19.662Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="jlange" data-post="9" data-topic="453448">
